The '''Learning Circle''' was a facility on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] of [[Kegan/Legends|Kegan]] that taught the Keganite youth the way of the [[General Good]] through a curriculum called [[The Learning]]. [[Control Guide]]s would send students who behaved poorly to the [[Re-Learning Circle]], where they were isolated in cells and directly brainwashed by headsets in sensory deprivation suits.<ref name="The Fight for Truth">''[[Jedi Apprentice: The Fight for Truth]]''</ref>

The Learning Circle was a self-sufficient [[City/Legends|city]] on its own, for it was located over two hours away from Kegan's [[Capital/Legends|capital]]. The school had its own recreational track, medical facilities, quads, and farmland. Moreover, the complex was protected by a series of [[Security Guide]]s, walls, alarms, and watchtowers. In [[44 BBY/Legends|44 BBY]], the Circle was closed when the people of [[Kegan/Legends|Kegan]] realized what was taking place within its walls and ousted as [[V-Tan]] and [[O-Vieve]] as [[Benevolent Guide]]s.<ref name="The Fight for Truth" />

